<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<body>
    <div id="headerwrap" style="background: url('/Images/NewHomePage/background.jpg') no-repeat center top; background-position: center center; background-size: 100% 100%; background-attachment: relative;">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row centered">
                <div class="col-lg-12 mt">
                    <h1 class="animation slideDown" style="color:white;">This website is a sandbox for my projects, focusing on new technologies involving .NET, Azure, and development best practices.</h1>
                    <p class="mt"><a href="@Url.Action("About", "Home")"><button type="button" class="btn btn-cta btn-lg">LEARN MORE</button></a></p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- /row -->
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container" style="padding-top: 0px; margin-top: 0px;">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-xs-12 desc" style="padding-top:20px;">
                <h3><b>Guitar Tab</b></h3>
                <a class="b-link-fade b-animate-go" href="@Url.Action("Index", "GuitarTab")">
                    <img width="350" height="200" src="~/Images/NewHomePage/guitar2.jpg" alt="">
                </a>
                <p>I've been collecting guitar tab for my favorite bands since 1997. I've then edited, standardized and ranked the quality as I learned to play them. <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "GuitarTab")">View Guitar Tab &raquo;</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-xs-12 desc" style="padding-top:20px;">
                <h3><b>Steam Analytics</b></h3>
                <a class="b-link-fade b-animate-go" href="@Url.Action("Index", "Steam", new { steamID = "76561197971691578" })">
                    <img width="350" height="200" src="~/Images/NewHomePage/steam.jpg" alt="">
                </a>
                <p>Tapping into my Steam Account via the <a href="https://steamcommunity.com/dev" target="_blank">Steam Web API</a>. I'm trying to develop better insights and interesting views of achievements. <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Steam", new { steamID = "76561197971691578" })">View Steam Analytics &raquo;</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-xs-12 desc" style="padding-top:20px;">
                <h3><b>World Cup Analysis</b></h3>
                <a class="b-link-fade b-animate-go" href="@Url.Action("Index", "WorldCup")">
                    <img width="350" height="200" src="~/Images/NewHomePage/soccer.jpg" alt="">
                </a>
                <p>A collection of statistics from all World Cups... <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "WorldCup")">View World Cup Analysis &raquo;</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-xs-12 desc" style="padding-top:20px;">
                <h3><b>Foo Fighters Gigography</b></h3>
                <a class="b-link-fade b-animate-go" href="@Url.Action("Index", "FooFighters")">
                    <img width="350" height="200" src="~/Images/NewHomePage/foofighters.jpg" alt="">
                </a>
                <p>This is a collection of Foo Fighter shows over the past 20 years. Much of this data was colloraborated together with <a href="https://www.foofighterslive.com" target="_blank">www.foofighterslive.com</a>, and is up to date until about 2016. <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "FooFighters")">View Foo Fighters Gigography &raquo;</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-xs-12 desc" style="padding-top:20px;">
                <h3><b>iTunes Listening Analysis</b></h3>
                <a class="b-link-fade b-animate-go" href="@Url.Action("Index", "iTunes")">
                    <img width="350" height="200" src="~/Images/NewHomePage/records.png" alt="">
                </a>
                <p>I've been saving my iTunes library files for analysis since 2006. This project is a result of this work. <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "iTunes")">View iTunes Listening Analysis &raquo;</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-xs-12 desc" style="padding-top:20px;">
                <h3><b>Game Development</b></h3>
                <a class="b-link-fade b-animate-go" href="@Url.Action("Index", "GameDev")">
                    <img width="350" height="200" src="~/Images/NewHomePage/unity.png" alt="">
                </a>
                <p>This is my attempt to create my own turn based strategy game with Unity3D... <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "GameDev")">View Game Development &raquo;</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>

